=head1 DESCRIPTION

The details of the address associated with the TRN information.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> AddressLine1 => Str

The first line of the address.


=head2 AddressLine2 => Str

The second line of the address, if applicable.


=head2 AddressLine3 => Str

The third line of the address, if applicable. Currently, the Tax
Settings API accepts the C<addressLine3> parameter only for Saudi
Arabia. When you specify a TRN in Saudi Arabia, you must enter the
C<addressLine3> and specify the building number for the address. For
example, you might enter C<1234>.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> City => Str

The city that the address is in.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> CountryCode => Str

The country code for the country that the address is in.


=head2 DistrictOrCounty => Str

The district or county the address is located.

For addresses in Brazil, this parameter uses the name of the
neighborhood. When you set a TRN in Brazil, use C<districtOrCounty> for
the neighborhood name.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> PostalCode => Str

The postal code associated with the address.


=head2 StateOrRegion => Str

The state, region, or province that the address is located. This field
is only required for Canada, India, United Arab Emirates, Romania, and
Brazil (CPF). It is optional for all other countries.

If this is required for tax settings, use the same name as shown on the
B<Tax Settings> page.



